<SLUG> BC-BKW-SPARKS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SPARKS MEET PHOENIX
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By PAMELA LEWIS  
 c.1998 Long Beach Press-Telegram  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Sparks continue their WNBA season-opening
three-game road trip today against the Phoenix Mercury at 1 p.m. at
the America West Arena.
</P>
<P>
   Lisa Leslie, who helped the USA national team win the gold medal
in the World Championships last Sunday, showed no signs of jet lag
as the Sparks' center scored 24 points and grabbed 12 rebounds in
the season-opening victory over the Utah Starzz Thursday. Guard
Tamecka Dixon added 18 points.
</P>
<P>
   The Sparks missed the playoffs last year when they lost their
season finale, 73-68, in overtime to the eventual Western
Conference champion Mercury, who are coached by Cheryl Miller. The
Sparks and Mercury split the four-game series last year. Phoenix
won both its games in overtime.
</P>
<P>
   Guard Briget Pettis knocked down a 3-pointer with 4.5 seconds
remaining as Phoenix won its opener at Sacramento, 73-70, Thursday.
Jennifer Gillom led the Mercury with 22 points.
</P>
<P>
   The Sparks play at Sacramento Tuesday before returning to Los
Angeles for their home-opener Friday against New York.
</P>
<P>
   - Pamela Lewis
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By The PRESS TELEGRAM, LONG BEACH, CALIFORNIA
</P>
</TEXT>
