matches _ including Iran and Yugoslavia _ that will make that task
very difficult. Just weeks after the U.S. Soccer Federation
outlined an ambitious $50 million developmental program to win the
World Cup by 2010, this American team already is reflecting some of
the changes envisioned for the future of soccer in the U.S. A good
showing in France will help continue the progress made in this
decade. (Parker, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
