<SLUG> BC-ADVERTISING-NOTES-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ADVERTISING NOTES 
</HEADLINE>
  (mk) 
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Campbell Mithun Esty in Minneapolis, majority-owned by
Interpublic Group of Cos., has named James White as chief creative
officer. White, 39, succeeds David Tree, 57, who continues as vice
chairman and will take a more active role in business development.
</P>
<P>
   White comes to Campbell Mithun from Long Haymes Carr in
Winston-Salem, N.C., a unit of Interpublic, where he had been vice
chairman and chief creative officer since 1995, working on
campaigns for accounts like BellSouth Corp.; Hanes, sold by Sara
Lee Corp., and Winston, sold by the R.J. Reynolds Tobacco Co. unit
of RJR Nabisco Holdings Corp. A successor to White has not been
named.
</P>
<P>
   Georgia-Pacific Expands Its Roster
</P>
<P>
   Georgia-Pacific Corp. has expanded its agency roster by naming
the New York office of Fallon McElligott to handle an unspecified
branding assignment for its packaged products division. Billings
were not disclosed.
</P>
<P>
   Fallon McElligott New York City, as the Minneapolis-based
agency's New York office is known, was selected after a two-month
review that also included the Merkley Newman Harty unit of Omnicom
Group and two agencies owned by Interpublic Group of Co.:
Carmichael Lynch in Minneapolis and Martin Agency in Richmond.
</P>
<P>
   Another Omnicom agency, the BBDO South unit of BBDO Worldwide in
Atlanta, will continue as the agency of record for the consumer
products sold by the division, which include Angel Soft toilet
paper and Coronet paper towels, as well as for corporate
advertising. BBDO South joined the Georgia-Pacific roster in March
when the previous agency for consumer paper products, Wells BDDP in
New York, announced plans to close.
</P>
</TEXT>
